title: Tarzan and the Jewels of Opar
creator: Edgar Rice Burroughs
description: LibriVox recording of Tarzan and the Jewels of Opar, by Edgar Rice Burroughs, read by Ralph Snelson. This is the fifth of Burrough's Tarzan novels. Tarzan finds himself bereft of his fortune and resolves to return to the jewel-room of Opar, leaving Jane to face unexpected danger at home. (Summary written by Sarah Jennings.) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org M4B format available
